{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdH7e7GW6t1jHpsriBwhQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. Tests pass.\n\n**The bug:** `orderTotalCents` applied the discount and rounded to the nearest cent **per line**, but the spec (and billing's expectation) is that the discount applies to the whole order subtotal, rounded **once**.\n\n**Why it drifts by a cent:** rounding each line independently accumulates rounding error. Concretely, the reported case — an order that should total $8.99:\n\n- Say two lines each priced so the true discounted total is 899¢ (e.g. subtotal 1000¢ at 10.1% off = 898.99 ≈ 899¢).\n- Split across lines, each line rounds up separately (e.g. 449.5→450 twice = 900¢), producing $9.00 instead of $8.99.\n\n**The fix** (`src/money.js`): sum the exact integer subtotal first, then apply the discount and `Math.round` a single time — matching the documented contract."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":317,"cache_read_input_tokens":23217,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":317},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3f606824-178b-42ce-ac5b-26d1bac4a7a9","uuid":"e6ba205b-e607-45cc-892c-c4853ffc7b72","timestamp":"2026-07-22T12:43:10.154Z","request_id":"req_011CdH7e5rfvQatPkKsW8zt8"}
